# Al-Rehla Cursor Rules (Wave-Based Launch)

## 1) Product Phasing Is Mandatory
- Build all Phase 1, 2, and 3 code paths early.
- Only expose UI entry points based on feature flags.
- Never expose future-wave entry points to regular users without a lock state.

## 2) God Mode (Role-Based)
- Privileged roles: `admin`, `owner`, `superadmin`, `developer`.
- Privileged roles must see all features regardless of flag mode.
- Regular users must see only effective feature access from flags.

## 3) Feature Flags Source of Truth
- Definitions and defaults: `src/config/features.ts`.
- Effective access + role bypass: `src/utils/featureFlags.ts`.
- Admin controls: `src/components/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx`.

## 4) Locked Feature UX Contract
- Never return 404 for a disabled feature click.
- Show `FeatureLockedModal` with a single consistent message.
- Keep teaser visibility for locked entries where UX requires anticipation.

## 5) AI Safety + Availability Contract
- Agent prompt must include current `availableFeatures`.
- Agent must not suggest or execute locked tools.
- If a user asks for a locked capability, respond with the approved fallback line and route to current-wave options.

## 6) Data Integrity Contract
- Family-tree lineage is represented by `treeRelation.parentId` in node JSON.
- Validators must run on load/save so hidden features still keep valid schema.
- Export/import must preserve tree relation data even when UI is locked.

## 7) User-Centric Decision Rule
- Every new UI/behavior change must answer: why this helps the owner daily.
- Prefer reuse over duplicate components.
- Before major edits, run a discovery pass with `rg` on App/Sidebar/state/modules.

## 8) Platform Access Persistence (Supabase/Vercel)
- Never block on permissions without first running `npm run access:doctor`.
- Access bootstrap source of truth is `scripts/bootstrap-access.ps1`.
- Required keys for full autonomous ops:
  - `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`
  - `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
  - `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
  - `ADMIN_API_SECRET`
  - `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`
  - `SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF`
  - `VERCEL_TOKEN`
- After keys are set, run `npm run access:bootstrap` once to persist user env + verify CLI auth.
